Table 9B  Incident dialysis patients with late referral status,* by primary diagnosis, Canada, 2020 to 2021 (percentage)
* Patients with a late referral status started dialysis less than 90 days after first seeing a nephrologist.
† For a list of all primary diagnoses captured by CORR, see Canadian Organ Replacement Register — Methodology Notes and Supplementary Information, 2012 to 2021.

Due to significant under-reporting of Quebec dialysis data between 2011 and 2019, data within this table is limited to the last 2 years. While dialysis data submission for Quebec recommenced in 2020, there still exists potential for under-reporting of incidence in 2020–2021.
Canadian Organ Replacement Register, 2022, Canadian Institute for Health Information.
